{"questionListItems":[{"id":"cluhz8nox0061124y4x5ose77","title":"How do I apply for mediation online?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8nox0062124yzwfuzlvl","body":"You can apply for mediation at the CMC's website at www.cmc.mlaw.gov.sg. You will need your Singpass to access this e-service.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8nox0063124y2rt3irhu","title":"What are the timing for mediation sessions?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8nox0064124yrotd1x8g","body":"Voluntary mediation sessions are held during office hours on weekdays and Saturday mornings.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8noy0065124ytf5vkgwe","title":"Where is CMC located?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8noy0066124y6eco75ld","body":"The CMC is located at 45 Maxwell Road, The URA Centre (East Wing), #07-11, Singapore 069118.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8noy0067124y3uql1a4h","title":"How can CMC help to solve my problems?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8noy0068124yd4vo8qyf","body":"You can use CMC's mediation service to speak to the person who is causing you the problem. This could be a neighbour, a family member, a landlord, a tenant/co-tenant, a friend, colleague or any other person that you may have a social, relational or community issue with. Once you apply for mediation, the CMC will invite the person that you wish to speak to for mediation. If the other person agrees, the CMC will arrange a mediation date and time that is suitable for you. You can use one or more mediation session to discuss and iron out any disagreement with the person that you have a problem with. Should you come to an agreement, the terms of your agreement can be written and signed by both of you.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8noy0069124y1bm1jgsc","title":"What kind of nature of cases is CMC able to take in?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8noy006a124yucefp52u","body":"<div>You can use CMC's mediation service to mediate any social, relational or community issues with your neighbour, regardless of whether you are staying in a public housing or private housing.                                                                                                                                                                                                                               Types of neighbour disputes that are suitable for the CMC mediation include </div><div>                                                                                                                                                       1.  Activities that generate unacceptable smell </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                               2. Activities that generate excessive smoke </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                                     3. Animal related complaints </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              4. Causing damage to property </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           5. Display of unacceptable behaviour or conduct </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                          6. Dripping of water from laundry or other sources </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                      7. Littering </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                8. Misuse or obstruction of common property </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                                9. Noise generated from activities done within a residence </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                      10. Noise generated from activities outside a place of residence </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                            1<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">1. Utterance of unacceptable words</span></div><div>Â </div><div><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">                                                                                                                                                                                                                              You can apply for mediation during office hours by calling the MINLAW Enquiry Line at 1800 2255 529 or apply online at the CMC website www.cmc.mlaw.gov.sg. You will need your Singpass to access this e-service</span></div>","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8noy006b124y1q5jdc7a","title":"Will HDB be kept in the loop if I mediate with my neighbour regarding noise?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8noy006c124yxp968upn","body":"Mediation is a private and confidential process. If your case was referred to the CMC by another government agency, all details regarding the mediation including the terms of agreement will be kept confidential. The agency will be notified only of the outcome of the referral.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8noy006d124y5adpezk0","title":"Can I request for mediation at my place?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8noy006e124y4lfwm6r0","body":"Mediation conducted by the CMC will be held at the government gazetted location which is currently at 45 Maxwell Road, URA Centre East Wing, Level 7.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8noz006f124yotjnw36c","title":"How come I have to pay and not the other party?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8noz006g124yx5tro59j","body":"The fee is payable by the person who is requesting to use the mediation service.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8noz006h124yyzt6olj5","title":"Who will be providing the solutions in the mediation session?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8noz006i124ytp66p6x7","body":"The CMC mediators will assist both parties to discuss and come up with solutions that they both can agree to.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8noz006j124y9vm3etdr","title":"How can CMC help me resolve a dispute between me and my landlord?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8noz006k124y7h9y57s9","body":"In order to use CMC's mediation service to talk to you landlord about your issues, you need to ensure that the issue is question is not covered by a tenancy agreement. If it is, CMC mediation is not suitable. If it is not, you can use CMC's mediation service to mediate with your landlord. You can apply for mediation during office hours by calling the MINLAW Enquiry Line at 1800 2255 529 or apply online at the CMC website www.cmc.mlaw.gov.sg. You will need your Singpass to access this e-service","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8noz006l124y3stpu62h","title":"What are the benefits of mediation?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8noz006m124ynrqdl3sl","body":"<div><div>The benefits of mediation include</div><ol><li>Private and confidential. Your identity and any issue discussed during the mediation is kept confidential.               <br/></li><li>Quick. It typically lasts about 2 hours.     <br/></li><li>Affordable. The person requesting for mediation only pays a one-time administrative fee of S$5 regardless of the number of mediation sessions. Â <br/></li><li>Solution-oriented. All kinds of solutions can be generated to resolve the issues. Parties can select those that are mutually acceptable. <br/></li><li>Flexible. Parties have the flexibility of coming up with out-of-the-box solutions that suit them.   <br/></li><li>Mends relationship. Provides an opportunity to mend relationships privately without unwanted publicity or embarrassment. <br/></li></ol></div>","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8noz006n124y96lwxf8t","title":"What can CMC do if the other party does not respond to CMC's invitation letters?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8noz006o124yfguoi7gd","body":"If the Respondent fails to respond after the invitation to mediate, the CMC will inform the Applicant and close the matter. You may wish to consider other legal options.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8noz006p124yt59omfk5","title":"What is the difference between voluntary mediation and Court referred mediation?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8noz006q124yqz708gc3","body":"Voluntary mediation is conducted only when both disputing parties has agreed to take part in the mediation process. Court referred mediation is mediation that is conducted as a result of an Order of Court. Attendance at a court referred mediation is compulsory for parties who are named in the court order.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8noz006r124yzelq7zwm","title":"How long is a mediation?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8noz006s124yu94p9fbu","body":"<div>Typically, a mediation session lasts about 2 hours. Some sessions may take longer. If the mediation goes beyond 4 hours, the mediator may adjourn to a second or third session should both parties wish to discuss further.Â </div>","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8noz006t124yxieqnzvc","title":"Does CMC mediate between spouses?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8np0006u124ys1a4cdro","body":"<div><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">You can use CMC's mediation service to mediate with your family members regarding the following issues: </span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">1. Care and maintenance arrangement for elderly, sick or disabled family members </span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">2. Disagreement on living arrangements </span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">3. Display of unacceptable behaviour or conduct </span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">4. Interest free monetary matter based on verbal agreement for amount involving less than $5000 </span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">5. Utterance of unacceptable words</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Â </span></div>","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}}],"webResult":null,"count":936,"agency":{"id":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","name":"Ministry of Law","code":"mlaw","homepageUrl":"https://www.mlaw.gov.sg","enquiryPageUrl":"https://eservices.mlaw.gov.sg/enquiry/","scope":"GLOBAL","emailDomainWhitelist":[],"type":"SCRAPED","minimumDayResponseTime":3,"responseTimeRange":10,"logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png","searchHint":"Legal Aid, Public Trustee","description":null,"trendingTerms":[],"hasSubjectTriaging":false,"subjects":[]},"currentPage":4,"matchedTokens":null,"agencyTopics":[{"id":729,"qcount":189,"title":"Precious Stones and Precious Metals Dealers","agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"priority":0,"subtopics":[{"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","id":730,"parentTopicId":729,"priority":0,"qcount":53,"title":"Reporting Requirement - Semi-Annual Return"},{"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","id":1454,"parentTopicId":729,"priority":0,"qcount":38,"title":"Regulatory Regime - CTR Filing / CDD matters"},{"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","id":735,"parentTopicId":729,"priority":0,"qcount":36,"title":"Registration and Renewal"},{"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","id":732,"parentTopicId":729,"priority":0,"qcount":17,"title":"Regulatory Regime - Guidance"},{"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","id":736,"parentTopicId":729,"priority":0,"qcount":9,"title":"myPal - Screening Function"},{"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","id":737,"pa